snippet.textDisplay:
This is my version for Ghostbusters 3. It would have been Chris Pratt as Oscar Barrett. With four additional cast members becoming Ghostbusters. People like Aziz Ansari, Kenan Thompson, Anna Kendricks and Randall Park. Aziz Ansari being a follower of Egon Spengler's work. Kenan Thompson being Winston Zeddmore's adopted nephew. Anna Kendricks being a paranormal investigator and the main person trying to re-start the Ghostbusters. Randall Park being a would be friend and associate of Chris Pratt's Oscar Barrett. Somehow some way they all get thrown together and become the new Ghostbusters. Whilst meeting and needing help from the original guys to see things through. Or so they think.

The film begins with Egon teaching a class about the paranormal. As he is now just a part time Ghostbuster. He has a wife and daughter as well. He's spending time with his family when he's summoned by a special alert watch for the Ghostbusters. It's revealed that it is December 31st 1999 where we find the original Ghostbusters (using CGI rendering) are battling a powerful entity called the self proclaimed Ghost God. Who's trying to suck the world through a portal before the new year begins. As it uses a little girl as a vessel. The Ghostbusters stop the Ghost God and seal the portal sucking in every ghost in existence with it. The spirit of the Ghost God is torn from the young girl but tries to pull her in with it. Thinking of his own daughter, Egon saves the young girl but loses his life as a result. As his soul is snatched from his body and pulled into the portal with all other ghosts of the world! Post 20 years later, the Ghostbusters have long been retired and disbanded! Ghosts are a thing of the past. Many newer generations think it was all a hoax to begin with. We find Oscar Barrett a washed up insurance salesman in NYC as he gets a call that the old firehouse is being condemned. When he arrives he meets Janine Melnitz with whom try everything to post pone its demolition. But to no avail, as it gets targeted for destruction in about a week or two. Oscar and Janine catch up as it is revealed he hasn't talked to his mom and step dad in years. We then find Anna Kendricks character Laura Rodman looking through tons of sorcery and spell books in an occult store once owned by Ray Stantz. Soon we meet a young scientist in Aziz Ansari's character Dennis Amin, working at a lab when mysterious happenings begin to spook him. He believes ghosts are trying return! Then we go to a local mechanic shop owned by Winston Zeddmore. Where his bumbling adopted nephew Kenan Thompson's character, Arthur Washington works. Where he is a talent with mechanical machinery, but some what accident prone. We then go back to Oscar Barrett as he enters his apartment building and runs into his buddy and former work associate Gregory Chester, played by Randall Park. Who tries to cheer Oscar up but comes off as a bit naive and a bit nosy. That's about as far as I got but its later revealed in the film that Laura was the girl that Egon saved from the Ghost God and paranormal visions of the it's apparent return by 2020 have hunted her ever since. Especially feeling responsible for the death of Egon, which she feels she has to make right. This time the Ghost God takes Spengler's grand daughter as a vessel. So they have to save her and of course NYC and the world. Peter and Dana would of had a daughter named Rachel who degrades Oscar's life choices like a over concerning sister and snagging mom. She would hate any and everything to do with talks of ghosts or Ghostbusters. Being a well to do woman married to a successful businessman, towards the end of the film she would have changed her ways by saving the old firehouse and helping to fund the new Ghostbusters. As she finally sees that Ghostbusting is making a positive influence on Oscar's life and it's making a difference in a world once again presented with ghosts.

We eventually see Bill Murray's Peter Venkman, Dan Aykroyd's Ray Stantz, Ernie Hudson's Winston Zeddmore, Sigourney Weaver's Dana Barrett and Annie Potts' Janine Melnitz all returning in present day as well. Not to mention Harold Ramis' Egon Spengler through special CGI body doubling. Since Rick Moranis is indifferently retired, he is only mentioned in passing. Would of loved to have had him in it as Janine's husband though!

What do you think so far? I know there is a actual Ghost busters 3 coming out in 2020 called Afterlife, but I just feel like it's too "StrangerThings" -esque to me. I dont like the kids or the setting. But being a big Ghostbusters fan, I will probably see it opening day. Thanks for reading!!

snippet.textDisplay: There are a lot of easter eggs in this trailer for the fans of the original, I am wondering just how much of what was in the original, Gozer for example, will reappear.  Jeremy is saying how different this will be, but other than the kids (which I hate, why did they have to do a bloody kids movie version!) I wonder how different it will really be.  We see what looks like a Terror Dog's claw on the hood of that car, we see the familiar green light that signifies a ghost in the original, we see a sign saying Shandor Mining (I am assuming the same Ivo Shandor from the original movie who built Dana's apartment building and formed the Gozer Worshippers?), we have the equipment from the original movie.  Yes, a fan movie I can see, definitely, but if every ghost apocalypse is connected to Shandor where do they go when they defeat him again here?  They could of, and to my mind should of, got a new team of adult Ghostbusters to pass the torch to and figured out a fresh way to get them ghosts to fight rather than obviously leaning heavily on nostalgia and a previous movies plot.

I thought you'd be smart enough to see the parents of these kids can be no older than 35 assuming the offspring of spengler were born in '84, which they weren't because he didn't have offspring in '89 (GB2) which means they are 30yrs old which also means the age of the grandchildren's mom at the time of having Finn wolfhard's character was 15 assuming he plays a 14/15 yr old kid. They should've just made the mom a ghostbuster and not these kids. Skipping a generation just because kids loved stranger things as this does scream "Young Ghost Things". I smell major retconning and easy cash grabbing for this. I hope you guys enjoy it. I'll keep my fingers crossed and hope the other Busters' offspring are adults and have a hand in this film.
